PLATINUM Stars’ sale to a business consortium from Cape Town and Joburg has left the people of Rustenburg with many questions.The club getting sold to unknown businessmen has left a bitter taste in the mouths of Phokeng residents, who were left scratching their heads after their questions went unanswered by those on the podium yesterday.Roger de Sa, Dikwena’s current head coach, confirmed yesterday that he is one of the businesspeople who have bought the club for a meagre R22,5 million.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuOeOrEUmjp9xFE1fXY0d0-H2evLn8nUUOrRcZnWZcDW5MLKhC9ASqqXDVFFJSQfrLaRVdIUdWy455-c1e83-HFA404-HsEyzNAIDDVT3m2mRY-5Dt6kM1wpCxC8qzOHmTfmPJtTbUtwTSq7pXKuocqLMXOkU9sCYPW156noUvLjwFULegdG0iqmq24o_pv8IG1NuooSskUtexJ_womkXM9HidD2L--Bjbs3YCA4mIftfUDX7QRhFgpMjRUTl-oqCUEQTD83U_SxaaOOfZqUWNAwA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzMuVbufudpk7EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
